## 1. Purpose
This procedure defines how [COMPANY] provisions access when a person joins, adjusts access when their role changes, and revokes access when they leave or their engagement ends. Timely, accurate access changes — especially prompt deprovisioning — are critical to preventing unauthorized access to systems and PHI.

## 2. Scope
Applies to all joiner, mover, and leaver events for employees, contractors, interns, and temporary staff across all in-scope systems: the [IdP — e.g. Okta], [AWS] (IAM Identity Center), [Snowflake], the [GitHub] organization, and all federated [SaaS] applications, including any system that handles PHI. This procedure implements `access-control-policy.md.template` and uses its authorization workflow.

## 3. Joiner — Onboarding & Provisioning
1. Onboarding **shall** be initiated by [HR / hiring manager] before the start date, identifying the person's role and any PHI access need.
2. Access **shall** be granted by **role**, not assembled ad hoc, using the predefined role/permission templates (AWS Identity Center permission sets, Snowflake functional roles, GitHub team membership, application roles).
3. The [IdP] account is created first and is the source of identity; downstream access is provisioned via federation/SSO wherever supported.
4. **MFA enrollment shall** be completed before access to any in-scope system is active (`identity-and-authentication-policy.md.template`).
5. Required security and HIPAA privacy training **shall** be assigned; PHI access **shall not** be granted until completion where required (`../people/security-awareness-training-policy.md.template`).
6. Each grant **shall** be authorized and recorded as evidence per the access authorization workflow.

## 4. Mover — Role / Access Changes
1. On any role change, transfer, or promotion, the [Manager] **shall** submit an access change request.
2. Access changes **shall** be processed as **add the new, then remove the old** so that residual entitlements from the prior role do not accumulate ("privilege creep").
3. The [System / Resource Owner] **shall** re-approve access to sensitive systems and PHI under the new role.
4. Privileged access **shall** be re-evaluated and revoked if no longer required (`privileged-access-management.md.template`).
5. The change **shall** be recorded; movers are a primary focus of recertification (`access-recertification-procedure.md.template`).

## 5. Leaver — Offboarding & Deprovisioning
1. [HR] **shall** notify [IT / Security] of any termination or end-of-engagement as early as the process allows; for involuntary terminations, notice **shall** precede or coincide with the event.
2. **Deprovisioning SLA:** all access **shall** be revoked within **[N hours]** of the effective termination time for standard departures, and **immediately / within [N hours]** for involuntary or for-cause terminations. Privileged access **shall** be revoked first.
3. The primary control is to **disable the [IdP] account**, which cascades to federated applications; system-specific revocation in §6 **shall** still be verified, as not all access is federated.
4. MFA devices, hardware tokens, and any company devices **shall** be reclaimed; long-lived credentials and tokens owned by the leaver **shall** be revoked/rotated.
5. Service accounts or shared resources the leaver owned **shall** be reassigned to a current owner.
6. Completion of revocation **shall** be confirmed and recorded as evidence within the SLA window.

## 6. System Deprovisioning Checklist
| System | Action |
|---|---|
| [IdP — e.g. Okta] | Disable account (suspends federated SSO); deactivate, then delete per retention. |
| [AWS] | Remove from IAM Identity Center group/permission sets; deactivate any IAM user and delete access keys; revoke active sessions. |
| [Snowflake] | Disable the user (`ALTER USER ... SET DISABLED=TRUE`); revoke roles; rotate any RSA key-pairs the user held; drop after retention. |
| [GitHub] | Remove from the org and all teams; revoke PATs/SSH keys; transfer owned repos/secrets; remove org-owner role if held. |
| [SaaS applications] | Deactivate via [IdP] SCIM/federation; verify any non-federated apps manually. |
| [Application] | Disable the application user account and revoke API keys/sessions. |
| Secrets | Rotate any shared secrets the individual could have accessed. |

## 7. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [HR] | Triggers joiner/mover/leaver events promptly and authoritatively. |
| [Hiring Manager / Manager] | Specifies role-based access; initiates change/leaver requests. |
| [System / Resource Owners] | Approve access to their systems and PHI. |
| [IT / Identity Administrators] | Execute provisioning/deprovisioning within SLA; record evidence. |
| [Security Officer] | Owns this procedure; audits SLA adherence and completeness. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 8. Exceptions
Exceptions to this procedure require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log.

## 9. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Deprovisioning timeliness is measured against the SLA in §5 and reconciled against HR termination records during access recertification (`access-recertification-procedure.md.template`). Orphaned or stale accounts identified through automated reporting (IdP, AWS credential reports, Snowflake login history, GitHub member lists) are remediated and tracked. Violations are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

